u_k=0,1$ for $k=0, 1, 2 \ldots$ . Properties (2.)-(4.) follow easily from this definition. More physics context for the problem is being prepared for publication, see also a related post at Physics.SE . Update : A physics paper describing these polynomials has been posted to arXiv , includes a reference to this question.

